The paper discusses the development and evaluation of an interruptibility-aware mobile robot system, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The study also involves human-robot interaction and social perception, which are relevant to the sub-categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to predict interruptibility, which is related to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
